  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1940-1943</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The picture shows the entrance hall of the ‘Savoja’ cinema in Tirana in approximately 1940. Signs inform visitors about access to seating on the first floor and the galleries. A poster advertises the movie ‘Manon Lescaut’ directed by Carmine Gallone and starring Alida Valli, Vittorio De Sica and Lamberto Picasso.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The movie was released in 1940 by the Italian production company ‘Grand Film’. The building was renamed ‘Teatri Kombëtar’ (National theatre) after World War II.</ab>
